29class RegExpMacroAssembler {
30 public:
31 // The implementation must be able to handle at least:
32 static constexpr int kMaxRegisterCount = (1 << 16);
33 static constexpr int kMaxRegister = kMaxRegisterCount - 1;
34 static constexpr int kMaxCaptures = (kMaxRegister - 1) / 2;
35 static constexpr int kMaxCPOffset = (1 << 15) - 1;
36 static constexpr int kMinCPOffset = -(1 << 15);
37
38 static constexpr int kTableSizeBits = 7;
39 static constexpr int kTableSize = 1 << kTableSizeBits;
40 static constexpr int kTableMask = kTableSize - 1;
41
42 static constexpr int kUseCharactersValue = -1;

44 RegExpMacroAssembler(Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone);
45 virtual ~RegExpMacroAssembler() = default;

47 virtual Handle<HeapObject> GetCode(Handle<String> source) = 0;

49 // This function is called when code generation is aborted, so that
50 // the assembler could clean up internal data structures.
51 virtual void AbortedCodeGeneration() {}
52 // The maximal number of pushes between stack checks. Users must supply
53 // kCheckStackLimit flag to push operations (instead of kNoStackLimitCheck)
54 // at least once for every stack_limit() pushes that are executed.
55 virtual int stack_limit_slack() = 0;
56 virtual bool CanReadUnaligned() const = 0;

58 virtual void AdvanceCurrentPosition(int by) = 0; // Signed cp change.
59 virtual void AdvanceRegister(int reg, int by) = 0; // r[reg] += by.
60 // Continues execution from the position pushed on the top of the backtrack
61 // stack by an earlier PushBacktrack(Label*).
62 virtual void Backtrack() = 0;
63 virtual void Bind(Label* label) = 0;
64 // Dispatch after looking the current character up in a 2-bits-per-entry
65 // map. The destinations vector has up to 4 labels.
66 virtual void CheckCharacter(unsigned c, Label* on_equal) = 0;
67 // Bitwise and the current character with the given constant and then
68 // check for a match with c.
69 virtual void CheckCharacterAfterAnd(unsigned c,
70 unsigned and_with,
71 Label* on_equal) = 0;
72 virtual void CheckCharacterGT(base::uc16 limit, Label* on_greater) = 0;
73 virtual void CheckCharacterLT(base::uc16 limit, Label* on_less) = 0;
74 virtual void CheckGreedyLoop(Label* on_tos_equals_current_position) = 0;
75 virtual void CheckAtStart(int cp_offset, Label* on_at_start) = 0;
76 virtual void CheckNotAtStart(int cp_offset, Label* on_not_at_start) = 0;
77 virtual void CheckNotBackReference(int start_reg, bool read_backward,
78 Label* on_no_match) = 0;
79 virtual void CheckNotBackReferenceIgnoreCase(int start_reg,
80 bool read_backward, bool unicode,
81 Label* on_no_match) = 0;
82 // Check the current character for a match with a literal character. If we
83 // fail to match then goto the on_failure label. End of input always
84 // matches. If the label is nullptr then we should pop a backtrack address
85 // off the stack and go to that.
86 virtual void CheckNotCharacter(unsigned c, Label* on_not_equal) = 0;
87 virtual void CheckNotCharacterAfterAnd(unsigned c,
88 unsigned and_with,
89 Label* on_not_equal) = 0;
90 // Subtract a constant from the current character, then and with the given
91 // constant and then check for a match with c.
92 virtual void CheckNotCharacterAfterMinusAnd(base::uc16 c, base::uc16 minus,
93 base::uc16 and_with,
94 Label* on_not_equal) = 0;
95 virtual void CheckCharacterInRange(base::uc16 from,
96 base::uc16 to, // Both inclusive.
97 Label* on_in_range) = 0;
98 virtual void CheckCharacterNotInRange(base::uc16 from,
99 base::uc16 to, // Both inclusive.
100 Label* on_not_in_range) = 0;
101 // Returns true if the check was emitted, false otherwise.
102 virtual bool CheckCharacterInRangeArray(
103 const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges, Label* on_in_range) = 0;
104 virtual bool CheckCharacterNotInRangeArray(
105 const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges, Label* on_not_in_range) = 0;
106
107 // The current character (modulus the kTableSize) is looked up in the byte
108 // array, and if the found byte is non-zero, we jump to the on_bit_set label.
109 virtual void CheckBitInTable(Handle<ByteArray> table, Label* on_bit_set) = 0;
110
111 // Checks whether the given offset from the current position is before
112 // the end of the string. May overwrite the current character.
113 virtual void CheckPosition(int cp_offset, Label* on_outside_input);
114 // Check whether a standard/default character class matches the current
115 // character. Returns false if the type of special character class does
116 // not have custom support.
117 // May clobber the current loaded character.
118 virtual bool CheckSpecialClassRanges(StandardCharacterSet type,
119 Label* on_no_match) {
120 return false;
121 }
122
123 // Control-flow integrity:
124 // Define a jump target and bind a label.
125 virtual void BindJumpTarget(Label* label) { Bind(label); }
126
127 virtual void Fail() = 0;
128 virtual void GoTo(Label* label) = 0;
129 // Check whether a register is >= a given constant and go to a label if it
130 // is. Backtracks instead if the label is nullptr.
131 virtual void IfRegisterGE(int reg, int comparand, Label* if_ge) = 0;
132 // Check whether a register is < a given constant and go to a label if it is.
133 // Backtracks instead if the label is nullptr.
134 virtual void IfRegisterLT(int reg, int comparand, Label* if_lt) = 0;
135 // Check whether a register is == to the current position and go to a
136 // label if it is.
137 virtual void IfRegisterEqPos(int reg, Label* if_eq) = 0;
138 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void LoadCurrentCharacter(
139 int cp_offset, Label* on_end_of_input, bool check_bounds = true,
140 int characters = 1, int eats_at_least = kUseCharactersValue);
141 virtual void LoadCurrentCharacterImpl(int cp_offset, Label* on_end_of_input,
142 bool check_bounds, int characters,
143 int eats_at_least) = 0;
144 virtual void PopCurrentPosition() = 0;
145 virtual void PopRegister(int register_index) = 0;
146 // Pushes the label on the backtrack stack, so that a following Backtrack
147 // will go to this label. Always checks the backtrack stack limit.
148 virtual void PushBacktrack(Label* label) = 0;
149 virtual void PushCurrentPosition() = 0;
150 enum StackCheckFlag { kNoStackLimitCheck = false, kCheckStackLimit = true };
151 virtual void PushRegister(int register_index,
152 StackCheckFlag check_stack_limit) = 0;
153 virtual void ReadCurrentPositionFromRegister(int reg) = 0;
154 virtual void ReadStackPointerFromRegister(int reg) = 0;
155 virtual void SetCurrentPositionFromEnd(int by) = 0;
156 virtual void SetRegister(int register_index, int to) = 0;
157 // Return whether the matching (with a global regexp) will be restarted.
158 virtual bool Succeed() = 0;
159 virtual void WriteCurrentPositionToRegister(int reg, int cp_offset) = 0;
160 virtual void ClearRegisters(int reg_from, int reg_to) = 0;
161 virtual void WriteStackPointerToRegister(int reg) = 0;

163 // Check that we are not in the middle of a surrogate pair.
164 void CheckNotInSurrogatePair(int cp_offset, Label* on_failure);

166#define IMPLEMENTATIONS_LIST(V) \
167 V(IA32) \
168 V(ARM) \
169 V(ARM64) \
170 V(MIPS) \
171 V(LOONG64) \
172 V(RISCV) \
173 V(RISCV32) \
174 V(S390) \
175 V(PPC) \
176 V(X64) \
177 V(Bytecode)
178
179 enum IrregexpImplementation {
180#define V(Name) k##Name##Implementation,
181 IMPLEMENTATIONS_LIST(V)
182#undef V
183 };
184
185 inline const char* ImplementationToString(IrregexpImplementation impl) {
186 static const char* const kNames[] = {
187#define V(Name) #Name,
188 IMPLEMENTATIONS_LIST(V)
189#undef V
190 };
191 return kNames[impl];
192 }
193#undef IMPLEMENTATIONS_LIST
194 virtual IrregexpImplementation Implementation() = 0;

196 // Compare two-byte strings case insensitively.
197 //
198 // Called from generated code.
199 static int CaseInsensitiveCompareNonUnicode(Address byte_offset1,
200 Address byte_offset2,
201 size_t byte_length,
202 Isolate* isolate);
203 static int CaseInsensitiveCompareUnicode(Address byte_offset1,
204 Address byte_offset2,
205 size_t byte_length,
206 Isolate* isolate);
207
208 // `raw_byte_array` is a ByteArray containing a set of character ranges,
209 // where ranges are encoded as uint16_t elements:
210 //
211 // [from0, to0, from1, to1, ..., fromN, toN], or
212 // [from0, to0, from1, to1, ..., fromN] (open-ended last interval).
213 //
214 // fromN is inclusive, toN is exclusive. Returns zero if not in a range,
215 // non-zero otherwise.
216 //
217 // Called from generated code.
218 static uint32_t IsCharacterInRangeArray(uint32_t current_char,
219 Address raw_byte_array,
220 Isolate* isolate);
221
222 // Controls the generation of large inlined constants in the code.
223 void set_slow_safe(bool ssc) { slow_safe_compiler_ = ssc; }
224 bool slow_safe() const { return slow_safe_compiler_; }
225
226 // Controls after how many backtracks irregexp should abort execution. If it
227 // can fall back to the experimental engine (see `set_can_fallback`), it will
228 // return the appropriate error code, otherwise it will return the number of
229 // matches found so far (perhaps none).
230 void set_backtrack_limit(uint32_t backtrack_limit) {
231 backtrack_limit_ = backtrack_limit;
232 }
233
234 // Set whether or not irregexp can fall back to the experimental engine on
235 // excessive backtracking. The number of backtracks considered excessive can
236 // be controlled with set_backtrack_limit.
237 void set_can_fallback(bool val) { can_fallback_ = val; }
238
239 enum GlobalMode {
240 NOT_GLOBAL,
241 GLOBAL_NO_ZERO_LENGTH_CHECK,
242 GLOBAL,
243 GLOBAL_UNICODE
244 };
245 // Set whether the regular expression has the global flag. Exiting due to
246 // a failure in a global regexp may still mean success overall.
247 inline void set_global_mode(GlobalMode mode) { global_mode_ = mode; }
248 inline bool global() const { return global_mode_ != NOT_GLOBAL; }
249 inline bool global_with_zero_length_check() const {
250 return global_mode_ == GLOBAL || global_mode_ == GLOBAL_UNICODE;
251 }
252 inline bool global_unicode() const { return global_mode_ == GLOBAL_UNICODE; }
253
254 Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }
255 Zone* zone() const { return zone_; }
256
257 protected:
258 bool has_backtrack_limit() const;
259 uint32_t backtrack_limit() const { return backtrack_limit_; }
260
261 bool can_fallback() const { return can_fallback_; }
262
263 private:
264 bool slow_safe_compiler_;
265 uint32_t backtrack_limit_;
266 bool can_fallback_ = false;
267 GlobalMode global_mode_;
268 Isolate* const isolate_;
269 Zone* const zone_;
270};

272class NativeRegExpMacroAssembler: public RegExpMacroAssembler {
273 public:
274 // Type of input string to generate code for.
275 enum Mode { LATIN1 = 1, UC16 = 2 };
276
277 // Result of calling generated native RegExp code.
278 // RETRY: Something significant changed during execution, and the matching
279 // should be retried from scratch.
280 // EXCEPTION: Something failed during execution. If no exception has been
281 // thrown, it's an internal out-of-memory, and the caller should
282 // throw the exception.
283 // FAILURE: Matching failed.
284 // SUCCESS: Matching succeeded, and the output array has been filled with
285 // capture positions.
286 // FALLBACK_TO_EXPERIMENTAL: Execute the regexp on this subject using the
287 // experimental engine instead.
288 enum Result {
289 FAILURE = RegExp::kInternalRegExpFailure,
290 SUCCESS = RegExp::kInternalRegExpSuccess,
291 EXCEPTION = RegExp::kInternalRegExpException,
292 RETRY = RegExp::kInternalRegExpRetry,
293 FALLBACK_TO_EXPERIMENTAL = RegExp::kInternalRegExpFallbackToExperimental,
294 SMALLEST_REGEXP_RESULT = RegExp::kInternalRegExpSmallestResult,
295 };
296
297 NativeRegExpMacroAssembler(Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone)
298 : RegExpMacroAssembler(isolate, zone), range_array_cache_(zone) {}
299 ~NativeRegExpMacroAssembler() override = default;
300
301 // Returns a {Result} sentinel, or the number of successful matches.
302 static int Match(Handle<JSRegExp> regexp, Handle<String> subject,
303 int* offsets_vector, int offsets_vector_length,
304 int previous_index, Isolate* isolate);
305
306 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static int ExecuteForTesting(
307 Tagged<String> input, int start_offset, const uint8_t* input_start,
308 const uint8_t* input_end, int* output, int output_size, Isolate* isolate,
309 Tagged<JSRegExp> regexp);
310
311 bool CanReadUnaligned() const override;
312
313 void LoadCurrentCharacterImpl(int cp_offset, Label* on_end_of_input,
314 bool check_bounds, int characters,
315 int eats_at_least) override;
316 // Load a number of characters at the given offset from the
317 // current position, into the current-character register.
318 virtual void LoadCurrentCharacterUnchecked(int cp_offset,
319 int character_count) = 0;
320
321 // Called from RegExp if the backtrack stack limit is hit. Tries to expand
322 // the stack. Returns the new stack-pointer if successful, or returns 0 if
323 // unable to grow the stack.
324 // This function must not trigger a garbage collection.
325 //
326 // Called from generated code.
327 static Address GrowStack(Isolate* isolate);
328
329 // Called from generated code.
330 static int CheckStackGuardState(Isolate* isolate, int start_index,
331 RegExp::CallOrigin call_origin,
332 Address* return_address,
333 Tagged<InstructionStream> re_code,
334 Address* subject, const uint8_t** input_start,
335 const uint8_t** input_end, uintptr_t gap);
336
337 static Address word_character_map_address() {
338 return reinterpret_cast<Address>(&word_character_map[0]);
339 }
340
341 protected:
342 // Byte map of one byte characters with a 0xff if the character is a word
343 // character (digit, letter or underscore) and 0x00 otherwise.
344 // Used by generated RegExp code.
345 static const uint8_t word_character_map[256];
346
347 Handle<ByteArray> GetOrAddRangeArray(const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges);
348
349 private:
350 // Returns a {Result} sentinel, or the number of successful matches.
351 static int Execute(Tagged<String> input, int start_offset,
352 const uint8_t* input_start, const uint8_t* input_end,
353 int* output, int output_size, Isolate* isolate,
354 Tagged<JSRegExp> regexp);
355
356 ZoneUnorderedMap<uint32_t, Handle<FixedUInt16Array>> range_array_cache_;
357};
